xpressions of dissent with the tools available to the documentary maker.Case studies include:Egypt's Ateyyat El AbnoudyLebanon's Jocelyne Saab Algeria's Assia DjebarTunisia's Selma Baccar Palestine's Mai MasriMorocco's Izza Génini Syria's Hala Alabdallah Yakoub  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCensorshipzAfrica, NorthxHistory. 0aCensorshipzMiddle EastxHistory. 0aDocumentary filmsxPolitical aspectszArab countries. 0aDocumentary filmszAfrica, NorthxHistory and criticism. 0aDocumentary filmszArab countriesxHistory and criticism. 0aDocumentary filmszMiddle EastxHistory and criticism. 0aWomen motion picture producers and directorszAfrica, NorthxHistory. 0aWomen motion picture producers and directorszArab countries. 0aWomen motion picture producers and directorszMiddle EastxHistory. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311078140340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748696079?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748696079zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748696079/original  a978-3-11-078140-3 Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA